allNotesData.title: Markdown Note Examples
allNotesData.body:
This note lists some common examples for a Markdown note, see below:  
## Headings  
# h1 Heading  
## h2 Heading  
### h3 Heading  
#### etc.  

## Emphasis  
**This is bold text**  
__This is bold text__  
*This is italic text*  
_This is italic text_  
~~Strikethrough~~  

## Lists  
##### Unordered  
+ You can use `+`, `-`, or `*`  
- to create your unordered list  
* just like this  
##### ordered  
1. item one  
2. item two  
1. item three  

## Links  
[link text](https://github.com/)  
[link with title](https://github.com/ "title text!")  

## Images  
(require online source to work)  
without title:  
![Total Eclipse](https://octodex.github.com/images/total-eclipse-of-the-octocat.jpg)  
with title:  
![Nyantocat](https://octodex.github.com/images/nyantocat.gif "The Nyantocat")  

## Horizontal Rules
